{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"rebar-debug COMPLETE — fix implemented, RED->GREEN + mutation-checked.\n\nFIX (src only, no existing test touched): centralized a bounded transient-retry on the shared git-write seam.\n- gitutil.py: new _TRANSIENT_HEAD_MARKERS=('could not parse head',), _is_transient_head_error, _with_transient_head_retry (3 attempts, 0.1s escalating backoff). run_git_write now composes _with_index_lock_retry(OUTER) o _with_transient_head_retry(INNER) o run_git — so txn.py (transition/claim), delete.py, compact.py, init.py ALL self-heal automatically.\n- event_append.py: wrapped _git_commit, _git_commit_paths, and the UU-recovery commit with the SAME helper (create/append/delete-events path). Marker kept tight to the proven signature so it never masks a real error; git commit fails at HEAD-parse BEFORE writing, so retry is idempotent.\n\nVALIDATION:\n- RED oracle tests/interfaces/store/test_txn_transient_retry.py injects 'fatal: could not parse HEAD' on the first transition commit -> pre-fix FAILS with the EXACT CI error (RebarError exit 2 ... could not parse HEAD, _lib_writes.py:358); post-fix GREEN (self-heals, status->in_progress, 2 commit attempts). Held out from the fix subagent.\n- MUTATION check: emptying _TRANSIENT_HEAD_MARKERS re-seeds the root cause -> oracle back to RED (exact error). Teeth confirmed.\n- Negative test: a non-transient commit failure still surfaces immediately (1 attempt, not retried).\n- No regression: original failing test_transition_open_children.py 5 passed; store+lifecycle tiers under -n 4 worksteal 579 passed; retry/index-lock/UU tests 18 passed; make lint + make typecheck clean.\n- Step-7 sweep: all store-path git commit sites now covered by the one helper; eval/criterion-preview fixture-repo commits are throwaway scratch repos (out of scope). Sibling bug a16d (concurrent-writer-storm, same signature) is materially mitigated by this retry but has its own deeper serialization AC — leaving it to its own ticket.\n- Replication: the real runner-FS transient is NOT locally reproducible (edf7 0/275+; my loop clean) -> confirmation is injection-based, matching the accepted edf7 pattern.\n\nNext: push through Gerrit; close after Verified +1."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784234293940139001,"uuid":"5dc4af42-b84a-47d5-b3c0-54651474966a"}